Package org.opensextant.giscore.events

Class Element

java.lang.Object
org.opensextant.giscore.events.Element
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, IGISObject, VisitableGeometry, IDataSerializable
public class Element extends Object implements IGISObject, IDataSerializable, Serializable
An element represents an XML element found in an XML type document such as KML. This is a limited representation that does not allow for nested element structures, although such a thing could be added in the future.
Author:
DRAND

    • addNamespace

      public boolean addNamespace(Namespace aNamespace)
      Add namespace. Verifies namespace prefix is unique in the list as required in a XML context with the XML unique attribute constraint. Duplicate prefixes are discarded and not added to the list. URIs may be duplicates in the list but its prefix must be different.
      Parameters:
      aNamespace - Namespace to add, never null
      Returns:
      true if namespace was added or if already existed in the list, otherwise false if not added because either argument was null or its prefix conflicted with one having another URI.

    • getChild

      public Element getChild(String name, Namespace ns)
      This returns the first child element within this element with the given local name and belonging to the given namespace. If no elements exist for the specified name and namespace, null is returned.
      Parameters:
      name - local name of child element to match
      ns - Namespace to search within. If ns is null then only the name field is checked.
      Returns:
      the first matching child element, or null if not found

    • getChild

      public Element getChild(String name)
      This returns the first child element within this element with the given local name regardless of the namespace. If no elements exist for the specified name, null is returned.
      Parameters:
      name - local name of child element to match
      Returns:
      the first matching child element, or null if not found
